release_note: Added daily challenges. You will receive a new challenge every day to try something new that might boost your mood.

Introducing the latest update for Mood Journal: Emotions Tracker! We ve listened to your feedback and made exciting improvements to enhance your experience: 1. Custom Activities: You can now add your own activities giving you the freedom to personalise your mood journal even further. 2. Improved Feelings Selection: We ve revamped our feelings picker by adding a search function and grouping feelings based on your chosen mood making it easier than ever to accurately track your emotions. Update now to enjoy these new features and continue your journey towards better mental health!

New practices with art therapy. When anxiety starts to creep up or when you suspect you re about to face some stress break out your Mood Journal and let your fingers guide you toward a more relaxed state of mind. The act of doodling itself may help calm you but you could notice some added benefit if you end up expressing your thoughts as you scribble. Maybe you end up carving solid lines into the paper to relieve tension or maybe you draw dark storm clouds to express a gloomy mood. Either way doodling can act as an outlet for emotional overwhelm.
